Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga and Gauteng Education MEC Panyanza Lesufi are expected to visit some of the families who lost their loved ones in the deadly minibus taxi crash. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga and Gauteng Education MEC Panyanza Lesufi are expected to visit some of the families who lost their loved ones in the deadly minibus taxi crash which claimed the lives of 18 school children in Bronkhorstspruit.A minibus taxi full of pupils collided with a truck on Groblersdal Road on Friday before bursting into flames.Two adults, including the driver of the vehicle, were also killed in the crash.Motshekga and Lesufi will be visiting two families, one of which lost four children in the crash.It's understood a general worker at one of the affected schools was also killed in the tragedy along with two of his children.The Gauteng Education Department's Steve Mabona says: From there we will move to a meeting with all family members to interact on funeral arrangements. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)